Section: web
Priority: optional
Description: Official SentinelOS browser v1.1.17 bookmark drag toolbar hotfix
 Sentinel Browser preserves the confirmed browser-first Download Guard flow and integrates
 a visible crypto-only Sentinel Wallet bridge with BTC, ETH/EVM, BNB, XRP, Solana, USDT,
 USDC, NFT foundation support, and Wallet v1.0.0 professional dashboard compatibility.
 Browser never stores wallet secrets or signs/broadcasts; Wallet provides explicit approval-gated blockchain login and transaction signing.
 v1.0.9 keeps the scalable SentinelOS Browser Home page, widens the default Browser window, removes automatic weather defaults, and uses a neutral Choose city state until the user selects a city.
 v1.1.0 adds a Browser-owned Tor toolbar switch, HTTPS indicator inside the address bar, and a Sentinel Wallet-backed blockchain provider bridge so clearnet pages and dApps can be opened without changing settings.
 v1.1.1 adds installer-option awareness so Basic Browser installs can hide Wallet/Tor controls and disable blockchain injection by user config.
 v1.1.2 adds Tor top-menu/right-click Change Identity controls plus WalletConnect/multi-chain provider compatibility foundation for EVM, Solana, and BTC/PSBT flows.
 v1.1.4 square-corners the homepage search-engine selector and hardens WalletConnect approval handoff by passing the exact browser request id into Sentinel Wallet so Wallet owns the visible approve/reject prompt.
 v1.1.5 sanitizes TOR country labels, square-locks the search selector, and hardens Phantom-style Wallet approval handoff.
 v1.1.6 fixes GUI installer option handoff, enables Wallet+dApp provider defaults for Wallet installs, adds Phantom/MetaMask detection compatibility, EIP-6963 announcement, wc: click/window.open capture, and Browser polling for Wallet approve/reject responses.
 v1.1.7 adds Phase 1 Sentinel Native Provider Core: shared local request/response schema, request envelope, wallet approval queue foundation, and no-QR injected-provider bridge readiness.
 v1.1.8 adds Phase 2 EVM native provider methods: real account return after Wallet approval, EIP-1193 request compatibility, EIP-6963 discovery, chain switching/add-chain handling, and message-sign request forwarding while preserving no browser secrets and no broadcast.
 v1.1.9 adds Phase 3 Solana native provider methods: public-key return after Wallet approval, Phantom-compatible window.solana/window.phantom.solana behaviour, Wallet Standard registration foundation, signMessage forwarding, and official Sentinel Wallet logo provider branding.
 v1.1.10 repairs the Phase 3 homepage search regex/navigation regression and uses the native-provider response-polling config key for dApp approvals.
 v1.1.11 gates ETH/SOL native-provider approval popups behind recent user action, deduplicates pending dApp requests to stop popup loops, and improves Solana provider return compatibility.
 v1.1.12 repairs the ETH/SOL provider discovery regression from v1.1.11 by restoring valid Wallet Standard JavaScript syntax and keeping dApp detection separate from manual approval/signing gates.
 v1.1.14 repairs the Uniswap ETH popup regression by caching approved EVM accounts per origin in the injected provider, returning repeated eth_requestAccounts/wallet_requestPermissions silently after approval, rejecting unsupported provider methods without opening Wallet, and removing long-lived hasBeenActive auto-popup permission.
 v1.1.15 restores the visible TOR toolbar/menu controls after the v1.1.20 installer could hide them when Tor was not selected; local Tor remains optional and routing stays off until user-enabled and ready.
 v1.1.16 adds user-created bookmark folders to the Bookmarks menu and favourites toolbar while preserving legacy flat bookmarks.
 Redteam hardening update: symlink-safe private paths, atomic writes, bounded bridge/import payloads, Tor button restore regression repair, and packaged bytecode cleanup.

