Architecture: all
Maintainer: SentinelOS Project <local@sentinel.os>
Depends: python3 (>= 3.9), python3-tk, python3-cryptography
Recommends: python3-argon2
Filename: pool/main/sentinel-wallet_1.1.14-2_all.deb
Size: 332792
MD5sum: 3fe0269116a27d412bf89f76dbe19663
SHA1: 46cc1067394f9ae5cae42c8afc276dc9e5553c38
SHA256: a400030fe57b56072ad8f06b456e0a768c492573059f14f0003ad58957fca316
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Description: Sentinel Wallet v1.1.14 Scrollable GUI content hotfix
 Sentinel Wallet is a local-first encrypted crypto-only wallet foundation.
 It provides a professional crypto-wallet style GUI with Dashboard first, encrypted wallet records for BTC, ETH/EVM, BNB Smart Chain, XRP Ledger, and Solana, plus USDT/USDC stablecoin and NFT local inventory foundations. It enables explicit user-approved local blockchain app-login signing and transaction signing for supported ETH/BNB/SOL paths, adds WalletConnect/multi-chain approval foundation for EVM, Solana and BTC/PSBT request flows, keeps the Wallets-tab Delete Wallet action, and keeps browser secret storage, card features, wallet-owned broadcast, and live network lookup disabled.
 v1.1.2 accepts an exact browser approval request id from Sentinel Browser so WalletConnect/dApp requests open the correct visible Approve/Sign vs Reject prompt instead of remaining in the bridge queue.
 v1.1.3 adds Phantom-style wallet approval UX: password prompt first, then Connect/Sign vs Decline for the exact dApp request.
 v1.1.4 keeps the Phantom-style password-first approval popup and aligns the Wallet gate with Browser v1.1.6 provider response polling and exact request focus.
 v1.1.5 adds Phase 1 Sentinel Native Provider Core: schema-versioned dApp request envelopes, native-provider response envelopes, pending approval queue readback, and no browser secret exposure.
 v1.1.6 adds Phase 2 EVM native provider approval results: approved eth_requestAccounts returns a selected local ETH/BNB public address, personal_sign/typed-data requests can return approved signed payloads, and Wallet still exports no secrets and performs no wallet-owned broadcast.
 v1.1.7 adds Phase 3 Solana native provider approval results, Solana public-key return, signMessage payload signing, Wallet Standard/Phantom-compatible status gates, and replaces Wallet icon assets with the official uploaded Sentinel logo.
 v1.1.8 repairs live Solana approval payload creation in the GUI prompt so approved solana_connect returns the selected SOL public key.
 v1.1.9 fixes browser-bridge --open launcher parsing so the Browser wallet toolbar button can open the Wallet GUI instead of the helper process exiting before Tk starts.
 v1.1.10 restores the secret-free Wallet GUI record/dashboard helper functions required by the Browser wallet button and browser-bridge --open path, fixing the wallet_gui_records NameError before the password/approval GUI can appear.
 v1.1.11 closes the Wallet GUI after approve/reject so the user returns to Browser, returns Solana publicKey fields at top level, skips completed bridge requests to prevent popup loops, and only shows approval prompts for exact Browser request ids.
 .
 v1.1.12 adds the Sentinel Banking foundation: a contained encrypted local-only section for user-created crypto Bank/Savings/Vault account containers, reward/interest eligibility metadata with no active yield claims, crypto receipt records, and CLI/GUI status gates. ETH/SOL native dApp baseline remains unchanged.
 .
 v1.1.14 makes the major Wallet GUI tabs vertically scrollable and adds visible scrollbars to large information panes to prevent bloated tab content from being clipped on smaller MATE/X11 displays.
 Redteam hardening update: symlink-safe private paths, atomic writes, bounded bridge/import payloads, and packaged bytecode cleanup.

